    <text type="letter">
        <body>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="loc_gt.00185_large.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <opener>
                <dateline> 
                    <name type="place"><handShift rend="printed"/>LIPPINCOTT'S</name>
                    <name type="place">MONTHLY MAGAZINE</name>
                    <date when="1891-01-16">Philadelphia, <handShift rend="manuscript"/>March 11 
                        <handShift rend="printed"/>18<handShift rend="manuscript"/>91</date>
                </dateline>
                <salute>Dear Mr Whitman.</salute>
            </opener>
            <p>The bearer of this is my son<ptr target="loc.04683_n1"/>&#8212;who inherits his father's admiration for you. He will explain his 
                mission &#38; if you can gratify him,
                I will greatly appreciate the kindness.</p>
            <p>The Whitman articles<ptr target="loc.05859_n10b"/> are 
                exciting considerable attention.&#8212;Will get up the notices after while 
                and send them to you for perusal.
            </p>
            <closer>
                <salute>Ever yours truly</salute>
                <signed>J. M. Stoddart&#8212;</signed>
            </closer>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001v" facs="loc_gt.00186_large.jpg" type="verso"/>
        </body> 
